Generate a longitudinal record for this specific synthetic patient: {{recipe.description}}

* your output should be a JSON object: {"records": {time: [[code_system, code_desc] or [code_system, code_desc, numeric_value, unit], ...], ...}, "finished": true/false}
* generate events sequentially by time
* set "finished": true only if you have completed the full record spanning from {{start_date}} to {{end_date}}; otherwise set "finished": false
* time: string key (ISO timestamp to appropriate precision; {% if record_type in ['claims', 'ehr-outpatient'] %}use date precision (YYYY-MM-DD){% else %}use datetime precision (YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM){% endif %} for {{record_type}}; use patient's birthday for static/person-level measurements)
* code_system: the vocabulary system for this code (must be one of: {{ allowed_code_systems | join(', ') }})
* code_desc: brief textual description of the measurement/event (not the code itself)
* for non-numeric events: output [code_system, code_desc]
* for numeric events: output [code_system, code_desc, numeric_value, unit] (unit is required when numeric_value is present)

* the first timestamp should be their birthday, with static measurements for gender, race, and ethnicity
* the rest of the record should span from {{start_date}} to {{end_date}}
* {{recipe.total_codes}} total events (CRUCIAL! do *not* generate fewer)
* approximately {{recipe.unique_codes}} distinct codes 
* approximately {{recipe.num_times}} time points
* average time between timestamps: approximately {{ "%.1f"|format(avg_time_between_timestamps) }} days
* {{recipe.avg_codes_per_time}} codes per time point, on average

--- example output ---

